{
  "texts": [
    "On the top of these pretrained layers, we separately trained the fully connected layers of three CNN classifiers: one on the set of blood samples and the other two on the sets of urine samples prepared adding two different salt solutions 28.",
    "Each CNN was trained to classify a given unlabeled sample into two categories, as either \"bladder cancer\" or \"not bladder cancer\".",
    "For classifier evaluation (testing part), the five-fold cross-validation technique was used due to the risk of overfitting.",
    "In this technique, the entire dataset of blood and urine samples was randomly divided into five folds and the testing part was repeated five times.",
    "In each trial, four folds (80% of the samples) were used to learn the network weights (of the fully connected layers) in the training and the remaining fold (20% of the samples), which was not used in the training at all, was used as the test set to calculate the performance metrics."
  ]
}